President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring Monday, October 5, 2015, as Child Health Day. The proclamation emphasizes the commitment to ensuring that children have the opportunity to lead healthy and productive lives. It highlights initiatives such as the Let's Move! campaign, which aims to provide nutritious food to students and promote physical activity. The Affordable Care Act is also mentioned, specifically the provision that allows young people to stay on their parents' health plans until age 26, as well as the prohibition of insurance companies denying coverage to individuals with pre-existing conditions. The proclamation also mentions the importance of addressing climate change to protect the health of future generations. The President calls upon families, educators, health professionals, and all levels of government to support and promote child health.